ack of opportunity, is the problem. We are all blessed with different gifts. Everything depends on what you do with yours\n\n- Ane\n|\nSee it first in your mind, then become it.\n\n- Steve Backley, The Champion in all of Us: 12 Rules for Success\n|\nThe truth, as much as people acted like they wanted to hear it, was sometimes too cruel and harsh.\n\n- Laura Kreitzer, Fallen Legion\n|\nTime spent in assessing one's self, is the time spent best.\n\n- Abhijit\n|\nBut, as your saints teach and we have always known, attachment enslaves you. Only those free from it see the world as it really is and have power over themselves and all things.\n\n- Lian Hearn, Autumn Princess, Dragon Child\n|\nAfter the knowledge of, and obedience to, the will of God, the next aim must be to know something of His wisdom, power and goodness as evidenced by His handiwork.\n\n- james\n|\nTo know your Enemy, you must become your Enemy.\n\n- Sun\n|\nIf the thought inspires you, and it feels good and right...it is yours, alone, to exercise. So get right on it!\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nVerily I say unto you all: Arise and shine forth, that thy light may be a standard for the nations.\n\n- Doctrine\n|\nThis is what the past is for! Every experience God gives us, every person He puts in our lives is the perfect preparation for the future that only He can see.\n\n- Corrie ten Boom, The Hiding Place\n|\nAh, it is impossible.''No, it is only very difficult - so very difficult that I shall be sure to accomplish it!\n\n- E.D.E.N. Southworth, Capitola's Peril\n|\nWith the Internet, we can choose the very communities we want to be a part of.\n\n- Alex Shakar, The Savage Girl\n|\nKnowledge is the most prized commodity in the entire universe, and it is infinite in its commodity.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nOnly if you are possible, everything will be possible.\n\n-